document_title: Botulinum poisoning: Symptoms, causes and prevention
subsection_content:
For botulinum poisoning, symptoms usually begin 12 - 36 hours after eating contaminated food. (3)
If the patient has symptoms of poisoning, even if the cause has not been determined, they should see an emergency doctor immediately.
